---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import heroHoverboards from '../assets/about/hero-hoverboards.jpg';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Hoverboard Havoc."
	pubDate={new Date('June 03 2026')}
	heroImage={heroHoverboards}
>
	<p>
		I love hoverboards. I loved them back in 2015 when they were suddenly everywhere, and
		I loved them through 2016 while they were busy catching fire and burning people's houses
		down, and I kept loving them long after everyone else had decided they were idiotic
		deathtraps and moved on to scooters.
	</p>

	<p>
		So when the rest of the world gave up, I doubled down. I bought twenty of them for 3000kr
		from the parents of a guy in Østfold who'd had enough of his scooter-repair business, and
		I've been taking them apart ever since, poking at their motor controllers, trying to get
		field-oriented control working, and bolting the guts to things that have no business
		moving. They're a cheap source of motor controllers and motors, and I like
		repurposing other people's trash.
	</p>

	<p>
		Sometimes this serves no purpose, just for the joy of it. My friend <a
			href="https://www.youtube.com/@robodurden/videos"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener">Robo Durden</a> would call me a brain degenerated consumer. He hates
		stupid fun projects. That's rather the point.
	</p>
</Layout>
